law.text:
Motor vehicle insurance companies shall give a five percent (5%) discount on comprehensive coverage on any motor vehicle equipped with any of the following antitheft devices:
Ignition or starter cutoff switch which is inserted into the ignition wiring of a motor vehicle that has flush or tapered door lock buttons;
Nonpassive, externally-operated alarm which is activated if any door, the trunk or hood is opened;
Internally-operated alarm which is activated if any door, the trunk or hood is opened, but which does not meet all the criteria in subsection (1) of KRS 304.20-420 or subsection (1) of KRS 304.20-430; or
Steering column armored collar which clamps on the steering column over the ignition lock.
